benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Remove tags from account

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios covered (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC09, TC11, TC13, TC15, TC19, TC20).
Invalid IDs and UUIDs covered (TC07, TC08, TC14).
Recovery from transient network failure covered (TC16).
Edge case with empty tagDef array covered (TC20).
gaps: Pagination behavior: DELETE responses are 204 with no body, but there is no test around listing or paginating tag definitions for accounts; if applicable, not tested.
Rate limiting: No tests addressing rate limiting or throttling for DELETE requests.
Caching behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE operation.
Explicit soft-delete semantics: If system supports soft delete vs hard delete, not explicitly tested; current tests assume hard delete.
Unauthorized/invalid token scenarios in more detail beyond TC15 (e.g., token expiry, revoked tokens) not exhaustively covered.
recommendations: Add a test for rate limiting/throttling on DELETE /tags to verify proper handling under high request load.
Add tests for caching headers pre/post-delete if API supports caching semantics.
Include more granular negative auth scenarios (expired/revoked tokens) beyond the generic 401/403 in TC15.
If applicable, add a dedicated test for soft-delete versus hard-delete behavior to confirm data retention rules.
Consider a pagination-related test only if endpoint can return a paginated tag list in related flows; otherwise, document exclusion.
